---
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="PatientBillGuide privacy policy — client-side processing, no PHI upload."
  pageClass="page-privacy"
  hideTitle
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Privacy Policy' }]}
>
  <section class="guide-hero guide-hero--privacy" slot="hero" aria-labelledby="privacy-hero-title">
    <div class="guide-hero__bg" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="guide-hero__orb guide-hero__orb--1"></span>
      <span class="guide-hero__orb guide-hero__orb--2"></span>
      <span class="guide-hero__grid"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="container guide-hero__inner">
      <div class="privacy-shield" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 64 72" width="64" height="72" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <path
            d="M32 4L8 14v18c0 14.4 10.2 27.9 24 32 13.8-4.1 24-17.6 24-32V14L32 4z"
            fill="url(#shield-grad)"
            stroke="rgb(255 255 255 / 0.35)"
            stroke-width="1.5"
          />
          <path d="M26 36l6 6 12-14" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          <defs>
            <linearGradient id="shield-grad" x1="32" y1="4" x2="32" y2="68" gradientUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
              <stop stop-color="#334155" />
              <stop offset="1" stop-color="#0f172a" />
            </linearGradient>
          </defs>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-hero__eyebrow">Trust · Transparency</p>
      <h1 id="privacy-hero-title" class="guide-hero__title">Your bill stays on your device</h1>
      <p class="guide-hero__lead">
        PatientBillGuide tools run in your browser. We do not ask you to upload medical bills to our servers
        or create an account to use calculators and checkers.
      </p>
      <p class="privacy-hero-date"><em>Last updated June 2026</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="privacy-pillars" role="list" aria-label="Privacy principles">
    <div class="privacy-pillars__item" role="listitem">
      <span class="privacy-pillars__icon" aria-hidden="true">🔒</span>
      <strong>Browser-only processing</strong>
      <span>Bill text and CPT codes are parsed locally — not sent to us for analysis.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="privacy-pillars__item" role="listitem">
      <span class="privacy-pillars__icon" aria-hidden="true">👤</span>
      <strong>No account required</strong>
      <span>Use every tool without signing in or sharing identity information.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="privacy-pillars__item" role="listitem">
      <span class="privacy-pillars__icon" aria-hidden="true">📋</span>
      <strong>No PHI collection by design</strong>
      <span>We do not intentionally collect protected health information through our tools.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="privacy-pillars__item" role="listitem">
      <span class="privacy-pillars__icon" aria-hidden="true">📖</span>
      <strong>Plain language</strong>
      <span>This policy explains what we do and do not do — no legal maze.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p>
    PatientBillGuide is a consumer education site with free billing tools. When you paste bill text or enter
    CPT codes, that input is processed <strong>in your browser</strong> using JavaScript and public CMS
    data files loaded from our CDN. We do not operate a backend that stores your pasted bills.
  </p>
  <p>
    That design choice matters for medical privacy: your itemized charges, diagnosis references, and account
    numbers never need to leave your device for our calculators to work.
  </p>

  <h2>What our tools do locally</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Fair Price Calculator</strong> — looks up Medicare fee schedule data by code and ZIP in your browser.</li>
    <li><strong>Bill Auditor</strong> — parses pasted line items client-side and compares against public benchmarks.</li>
    <li><strong>EOB Analyzer</strong> — extracts columns from pasted EOB text without server upload.</li>
    <li><strong>Dispute Letter Builder</strong> — generates editable text from your inputs; you copy and send it yourself.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Public data files (MPFS, NCCI, ZIP-to-locality maps) are static JSON served from our host — the same for
    every visitor. Your personal bill content is not written into those files.
  </p>

  <h2>What we may collect</h2>
  <h3>Server logs</h3>
  <p>
    Like most websites, our hosting provider (Cloudflare Pages) may log standard technical data when you
    load pages: IP address, browser type, pages requested, timestamps. These logs support security,
    abuse prevention, and performance — not medical analysis.
  </p>
  <h3>Analytics</h3>
  <p>
    We may add privacy-conscious analytics after launch to understand which pages help users most. If we
    enable analytics, we will prefer tools that minimize personal data and honor Do Not Track where
    applicable. This page will be updated before any analytics go live.
  </p>
  <h3>Advertising</h3>
  <p>
    We plan to use Google AdSense after the site meets program requirements. Ad networks may use cookies
    and device identifiers under their own policies. We will update this policy and, where required,
    display consent controls before enabling personalized ads.
  </p>

  <h2>What we do not do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Sell your medical bill content — we never receive it through our tools.</li>
    <li>Require Social Security numbers, insurance member IDs, or date of birth to use calculators.</li>
    <li>Provide medical advice, legal advice, or insurance enrollment services.</li>
    <li>Share data with debt collectors, providers, or insurers on your behalf.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies &amp; local storage</h2>
  <p>
    Core tools work without cookies. Third-party services (ads, embedded widgets if added later) may set
    their own cookies. You can clear site data through your browser settings at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    PatientBillGuide is intended for adults managing their own healthcare bills. We do not knowingly collect
    personal information from children under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We will post updates on this page with a revised "last updated" date. Material changes (such as enabling
    ads or analytics) will be called out at the top of the page when they take effect.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Privacy questions: <a href="mailto:contact@patientbillguide.com">contact@patientbillguide.com</a> or our
    <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    See also: <a href="/terms/">Terms of Use</a> · <a href="/disclaimer/">Disclaimer</a> ·
    <a href="/methodology/data-sources/">Data sources</a>
  </p>

  <section class="privacy-footer-band" aria-label="Privacy commitment">
    <p>
      <strong>Bottom line:</strong> We built PatientBillGuide so you can research bills without handing
      them to another company. Your paste buffer is yours.
    </p>
  </section>
</LegalLayout>

<style is:global>
  .page-privacy .legal-page__body {
    --guide-accent: #475569;
    --guide-accent-bg: #f8fafc;
    --guide-accent-border: #cbd5e1;
  }

  .guide-hero--privacy {
    --hero-accent: #64748b;
    --hero-accent-light: #94a3b8;
    --hero-bg: linear-gradient(165deg, #020617 0%, #0f172a 40%, #1e293b 100%);
  }

  .privacy-shield {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    filter: drop-shadow(0 8px 24px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.4));
    animation: privacy-shield-pulse 4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes privacy-shield-pulse {
    0%, 100% { transform: scale(1); }
    50% { transform: scale(1.04); }
  }

  .privacy-hero-date {
    margin: var(--space-md) 0 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 0.65);
  }

  .privacy-pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(13rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
    padding: 0;
  }

  .privacy-pillars__item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgb(15 23 42 / 0.06);
    transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }

  .privacy-pillars__item:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgb(15 23 42 / 0.1);
  }

  .privacy-pillars__icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .privacy-pillars__item strong {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #0f172a;
  }

  .privacy-pillars__item span:last-child {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .privacy-footer-band {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .privacy-footer-band p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 0.92);
  }

  .privacy-footer-band strong {
    color: #94a3b8;
  }
</style>
